00:56:24.935 --> 00:56:25.560 align:middle line:90%
AUDIENCE: Yeah.

00:56:25.560 --> 00:56:28.422 align:middle line:84%
Because I don't think we
did it in this lecture.

00:56:28.422 --> 00:56:29.130 align:middle line:90%
HONG LIU: We did.

00:56:29.130 --> 00:56:29.630 align:middle line:90%
Yeah.

00:56:29.630 --> 00:56:31.020 align:middle line:84%
Yeah, at the end
of last lecture.

00:56:31.020 --> 00:56:32.353 align:middle line:90%
Yeah, let me just write it down.

00:56:32.353 --> 00:56:42.090 align:middle line:84%
So the photon propagator
depends on this parameter xi.

00:56:42.090 --> 00:56:46.470 align:middle line:84%
For xi equal to 1, the
photon propagator--

00:56:46.470 --> 00:56:48.630 align:middle line:90%
if I call it D mu nu, yeah.

00:56:48.630 --> 00:56:50.760 align:middle line:84%
Anyway, let me
just write it down.

00:56:50.760 --> 00:56:54.015 align:middle line:84%
For xi equal to 1, this
is just given by eta mu nu

00:56:54.015 --> 00:56:56.530 align:middle line:90%
k squared minus i epsilon.

00:56:56.530 --> 00:56:59.310 align:middle line:90%
So this is for xi equal to 1.

00:56:59.310 --> 00:57:02.760 align:middle line:84%
So for xi not equal
to 1, so yeah.

00:57:02.760 --> 00:57:04.800 align:middle line:90%
So this is for xi equal to 1.

00:57:04.800 --> 00:57:06.390 align:middle line:84%
For xi not equal
to 1, then there

00:57:06.390 --> 00:57:09.530 align:middle line:90%
are some additional terms.

00:57:09.530 --> 00:57:10.190 align:middle line:90%
Yes?

00:57:10.190 --> 00:57:12.398 align:middle line:84%
AUDIENCE: I might be leaving
the scope of this class,

00:57:12.398 --> 00:57:14.905 align:middle line:84%
but the weak force has a
carrier that has mass, right?

00:57:14.905 --> 00:57:15.530 align:middle line:90%
HONG LIU: Yeah.

00:57:15.530 --> 00:57:17.030 align:middle line:84%
AUDIENCE: And it's
called a fermion.

00:57:17.030 --> 00:57:17.710 align:middle line:90%
HONG LIU: Right.

00:57:17.710 --> 00:57:19.885 align:middle line:84%
AUDIENCE: So that is
possible to construct.

00:57:19.885 --> 00:57:21.010 align:middle line:90%
HONG LIU: Yeah, yeah, yeah.

00:57:21.010 --> 00:57:21.510 align:middle line:90%
Yeah.

00:57:21.510 --> 00:57:24.450 align:middle line:84%
Again, this mechanism
is what's responsible

00:57:24.450 --> 00:57:26.903 align:middle line:84%
